      "description": "Up for sale is a mechanically sound 2006 Porsche 911 Carrera S (997.1) featuring the 3.8L M97 horizontally opposed six-cylinder engine. This naturally aspirated powerplant delivers 355 hp through a 6-speed manual transaxle with a short-throw shifter. The vehicle is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), utilizing electronic damping control for superior roll stiffness and mid-corner composure. Recent preventative maintenance includes an updated Air-Oil Separator (AOS) and a comprehensive cooling system flush. The braking hardware consists of four-piston aluminum monobloc fixed calipers paired with cross-drilled rotors, ensuring minimal fade under high thermal loads. This is a driver-spec example with a rigid chassis and communicative hydraulic steering rack, ideal for the enthusiast seeking a visceral connection to the road.",
